    "recap_headline": "The University of Texas at Austin Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AUSTIN, Texas \u2014\nThe second-ranked University of Texas baseball team dropped its first contest of the season, falling to Ole Miss, 9-8 in 11 innings at UFCU Disch-Falk Field on Friday night.\nWith the loss, the Longhorns' season-opening winning streak was halted at 16 games, matching Texas' best start to a season since 2005.\nIn the bottom of the 11\nth\n, the Longhorns (16-1, 0-1 SEC) put the tying tally\u00a0on first and brought the winning run to the plate, but Ole Miss righty Landon Waters (1) slammed the door with a strikeout.\nTexas also found itself down to its final strike in the ninth, but\nTemo Becerra\nnotched a game-tying single to force extra innings.\nAcross the 4-hour, 34-minute contest, the Longhorns led for 4 \u00bd frames, coming one out away from registering a win in the Southeastern Conference opener.\nInstead, right fielder Tristan Bissetta launched a go-ahead grand slam to vault the Rebels in front, 8-7.\nIn the defeat, Texas totaled three home runs, capped off by\nAnthony Pack Jr.'s\nthree-run shot in the eighth. Pack Jr.'s fourth blast of the season padded the Longhorns' lead to 7-3.\nEthan Mendoza\nand\nCasey Borba\nalso left the yard, smacking homers in the third and fourth, respectively. Mendoza mashed a game-tying three-run jack before Borba smacked his fifth round-tripper in as many games one frame later.\nOle Miss righty Tyler Rabe (3-0) earned the victory, striking out five over two innings in relief.\nMeanwhile, Texas right-hander\nBrett Crossland\n(1-1) was tagged with the loss. Crossland struck out four of the six batters he faced, but a hit batsman came around to score the decisive run.\nThe Longhorns will look to even the series against the Rebels on Saturday. First pitch is set for 2:30 p.m. at UFCU Disch-Falk Field."
  },
